Hi Rees. I only partially agree with that sentiment.  If we are talking about people with a 
reasonable degree of critical thinking and mental stability, then you have my full buy-in 
on that concept.  

However, it&#39;s my opinion there are *plenty* of people out there who should never touch a 
box of any flavor with a 10-foot pole, and having people who are mentally and/or 
emotionally unstable and who lack critical thinking, just mucks up the works and makes 
the rest of us look bad.  

ie:  People who believe and promote the idea that a &quot;murderous reptilian race&quot; is 
communicating through the DR60.  Yeah, you know...  I really don&#39;t want to be put in the 
same category with them, just because I own a DR60.  But rest assured, I got an email one 
time from someone assuming that of me, letting me know that she was a believer too!  
OMG!!!!!  

Margaret   

